_:Ndb231572202b4fe89c1743b31f13425e <http://schema.org/description> "We publish statistics on benefits, pensions, employment programmes, income distribution and other subjects we are responsible for." .
_:N5bbf93614e06415c891e428fbe14b0f8 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://schema.org/ListItem> .
_:Ndb231572202b4fe89c1743b31f13425e <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"published-and-upcoming-statistics\">Published and upcoming statistics</h2>\n\n<p>We publish Official and National Statistics on a regular basis. They provide accurate and impartial information about Department for Work and Pensions (<abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr>) benefits and related subjects.</p>\n\n<div class=\"call-to-action\">\n  <p>Browse our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">statistics by theme</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Use search terms and filters to find <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics?keywords=&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=department-for-work-pensions&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=\">published statistics</a> and details of <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/announcements?utf8=%E2%9C%93&amp;organisations%5B%5D=department-for-work-pensions\">upcoming statistics in our statistics release calendar</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Find details of developments coming to our statistics in our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-statistical-work-programme\">statistical work programme</a>.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"ad-hoc-statistics\">Ad hoc statistics</h3>\n\n<p>We also publish <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ad-hoc-statistical-publications-list\">ad hoc statistics</a>. These are published in response to specific questions and are not part of our regular Official and National Statistics publications.</p>\n\n<p>View details of our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/list-of-scheduled-upcoming-ad-hoc-statistical-releases\">upcoming ad hoc statistics</a>.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"management-information-and-ad-hoc-analyses\">Management information and ad hoc analyses</h3>\n\n<p>We also publish <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-ad-hoc-analyses\">management information and ad hoc analyses</a> that are not classified as statistics (or research). These are published in the interests of transparency and are not part of our regular Official and National Statistics publications.</p>\n\n<p>View details of our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/list-of-upcoming-releases-of-management-information-and-ad-hoc-analyses\">upcoming management information and ad hoc analyses</a>.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"freedom-of-information-requests-related-to-statistics\">Freedom of Information requests related to statistics</h3>\n\n<p>We also publish our responses to <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-foi-releases\">Freedom of Information requests related to <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> statistics</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"data-analysis-tools\">Data analysis tools</h2>\n\n<p>Explore <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> data in more depth using our data analysis tools.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"data-visualisations\">Data visualisations</h3>\n\n<p>You can explore and customise <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> statistics using the following interactive data visualisations:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/metadata/dashboards/bc/index.html\">Benefit Cap</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/metadata/dashboards/uch/index.html\">Households on Universal Credit</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/metadata/dashboards/pip/index.html\">Personal Independence Payment (<abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr>)</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3 id=\"stat-xplore\">Stat-Xplore</h3>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/\">Stat-Xplore</a> is an online tool that allows the creation and  download of customised statistical tables, as well as data visualisation through interactive charts. It currently holds statistics on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Alternative Claimant Count</li>\n  <li>Attendance Allowance (<abbr title=\"Attendance Allowance\">AA</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>Benefit Cap</li>\n  <li>Benefit Combinations</li>\n  <li>Bereavement Benefits</li>\n  <li>Bereavement Support Payment</li>\n  <li>Carer’s Allowance</li>\n  <li>Child Maintenance Service</li>\n  <li>Children in Low Income Families</li>\n  <li>Disability Living Allowance (<abbr title=\"Disability Living Allowance\">DLA</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>Employment and Support Allowance (<abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>\n<abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> Work Capability Assessments</li>\n  <li>Family Resources Survey</li>\n  <li>Households Below Average Income</li>\n  <li>Housing Benefit (<abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>Incapacity Benefit and Severe Disablement Allowance</li>\n  <li>Income Support (<abbr title=\"Income Support\">IS</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit (<abbr title=\"Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit\">IIDB</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>Jobseekers Allowance (<abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>National Insurance number allocations to adult overseas nationals</li>\n  <li>Pension Credit</li>\n  <li>Pensioner Income</li>\n  <li>Personal Independence Payment (<abbr title=\"Personal Independence Payment\">PIP</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>Population Estimates</li>\n  <li>Sanction decisions for:\n    <ul>\n      <li>Jobseeker’s Allowance (<abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>)</li>\n      <li>Employment and Support Allowance (<abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>)</li>\n      <li>Income Support (<abbr title=\"Income Support\">IS</abbr>)</li>\n      <li>Universal Credit (<abbr title=\"Universal Credit\">UC</abbr>)</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n  <li>State Pension</li>\n  <li>Support for Mortgage Interest</li>\n  <li>Universal Credit</li>\n  <li>Widow’s Benefit</li>\n  <li>Work and Health Programme</li>\n  <li>Work Programme</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"changes-to-dwp-statistical-geographies\">Changes to <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> statistical geographies</h2>\n\n<p>Due to increasing demand from users, <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> is making improvements to the published geography information in its National and Official statistics releases. This includes data released on <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/\">Stat-Xplore</a>. Read our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-statistical-geographies-in-national-and-official-statistics\"><abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> statistical geographies note</a> for more information about the changes.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">\n<abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> statistics and contacts by theme</h2>\n\n<p>Browse our regular statistical releases by theme below.</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#children-families-and-bereavement\">Children, families and bereavement</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#employment-support-schemes\">Employment support schemes</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#equality-information\">Equality information</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#health-disability-and-care\">Health, disability and care</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#housing-and-heating\">Housing and heating</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#income-and-living-standards\">Income and living standards</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#pensions-and-older-people\">Pensions and older people</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#spending-fraud-and-error\">Spending, fraud and error</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#work-and-unemployment\">Work and unemployment</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3 id=\"children-families-and-bereavement\">Children, families and bereavement</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Bereavement Benefit</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Bereavement Support Payment</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/family-based-child-maintenance-arrangements-statistics\">Child maintenance arrangements made after speaking to <abbr title=\"Child Maintenance\">CM</abbr> Options</a> – Estimated numbers of different types of child maintenance arrangement made after speaking to Child Maintenance (<abbr title=\"Child Maintenance\">CM</abbr>) Options from survey data. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cm.analysis.research@dwp.gov.uk\">cm.analysis.research@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-on-the-2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme\">Child Maintenance Service statistics</a> – Statistics on cases processed under the 2012 statutory child maintenance scheme.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cm.analysis.research@dwp.gov.uk\">cm.analysis.research@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-statistics-29-april-2013-to-11-april-2024/universal-credit-childcare-element-statistics-march-2021-to-february-2024\">Childcare element statistics</a> – Statistics about households receiving Universal Credit childcare element.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:ucad.briefinganalysis@dwp.gov.uk\">ucad.briefinganalysis@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/child-support-agency-quarterly-summary-statistics--2\">Child Support Agency (CSA) statistics</a> – Statistics on the CSA statutory child maintenance schemes and CSA case closures.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cm.analysis.research@dwp.gov.uk\">cm.analysis.research@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/children-in-out-of-work-benefit-households--2\">Children in out-of-work benefit households</a> – Numbers of children living in households where a parent or guardian claimed out-of-work benefits.  This series ended in 2018.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/children-in-low-income-families-local-area-statistics\">Children in low income families: local area statistics</a> – Number and percentage of children living in relative and absolute low income families. Contact: <a href=\"mailto:russ.bentley@dwp.gov.uk\">russ.bentley@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/esf-support-for-families-with-multiple-problems-statistics\">European Social Fund (<abbr title=\"European Social Fund\">ESF</abbr>) support for families with multiple problems (ceased)</a> – Statistics on the <abbr title=\"European Social Fund\">ESF</abbr> support for families with multiple problems programme. This series ended in October 2015.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/in-work-credit-statistics-on-start-ups--3\">In Work Credit (ceased)</a> – Take-up of the In Work Credit (IWC), a financial incentive available to lone parents moving into work. This series ended in May 2014.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/income-support-lone-parent-regime-figures-on-sanctions-and-work-focused-interviews--2\">Income Support lone parent regime</a> – This statistical series has ended. The statistics are now included in our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">benefits statistical summaries</a> and <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions\">benefit sanctions statistics</a>.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/lone-parents-receiving-jsa-monthly-claimant-count\">Lone parents receiving Jobseeker’s Allowance</a> – Number of lone parents receiving <abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>. This series ended in May 2018.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/maternity-allowance-quarterly-statistics\">Maternity Allowance</a> – Number of women claiming Maternity Allowance.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/separated-families-population-statistics\">Separated families statistics</a> – Estimates relating to separated families and their child maintenance arrangements.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cm.analysis.research@dwp.gov.uk\">cm.analysis.research@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/social-justice-outcomes-framework-family-stability-indicator\">Social Justice outcomes framework: family stability indicator</a> – Family stability indicator results. This series was last published in March 2016.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Widow’s Benefit</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/troubled-families-statistics\">Troubled Families programme</a> – Statistics on benefits and employment for individuals and households on the programme. This statistical series has ended.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-and-child-tax-credit-claimants-statistics-related-to-the-policy-to-provide-support-for-a-maximum-of-2-children\">Universal Credit and Child Tax Credit claimants: statistics related to the policy to provide support for a maximum of 2 children</a> – Statistics about the policy that provides support for a maximum of 2 children in Universal Credit and Child Tax Credit. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:ucad.briefinganalysis@dwp.gov.uk\">ucad.briefinganalysis@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"employment-support-schemes\">Employment support schemes</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/access-to-work-statistics\">Access to Work recipients</a> – Statistics on the number of people who had Access to Work provision approved. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:access.toworkstatistics@dwp.gov.uk\">access.toworkstatistics@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-cfo-european-social-fund-2014-to-2020-statistics\"><abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> <abbr title=\"co-financing organisation\">CFO</abbr> European Social Fund (<abbr title=\"European Social Fund\">ESF</abbr>) 2014 to 2020</a> – Statistics on the European Social Fund (<abbr title=\"European Social Fund\">ESF</abbr>) 2014 to 2020 employment programme operated by <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> as a co-financing organisation (<abbr title=\"co-financing organisation\">CFO</abbr>) in England. This statistical series has ended.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/esf-support-for-families-with-multiple-problems-statistics\">European Social Fund (<abbr title=\"European Social Fund\">ESF</abbr>) support for families with multiple problems (ceased)</a> – Statistics on the <abbr title=\"European Social Fund\">ESF</abbr> support for families with multiple problems programme. This series ended in October 2015.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/help-to-work-quarterly-statistics\">Help to Work</a> – a range of options that helped long-term unemployed people into work. This series ended in March 2018.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/income-support-lone-parent-regime-figures-on-sanctions-and-work-focused-interviews--2\">Income Support lone parent regime</a> – This statistical series has ended. The statistics are now included in our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">benefits statistical summaries</a> and <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions\">benefit sanctions statistics</a>.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-statistics-on-the-six-month-offer--2\"><abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>: Six Month Offer (ceased)</a> – Take-up of the Six Month Offer, a recruitment subsidy for job seekers that ended in March 2011.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-statistics-on-the-young-persons-guarantee-ypg\"><abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>: Young Person’s Guarantee (<abbr title=\"Young Person's Guarantee\">YPG</abbr>)</a> – Statistics on <abbr title=\"Young Person's Guarantee\">YPG</abbr>, which offered up to 24 weeks full-time training for unemployed young people. This series ended in April 2011.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pre-work-programme-and-get-britain-working#new-enterprise-allowance\">New Enterprise Allowance (<abbr title=\"New Enterprise Allowance\">NEA</abbr>)</a> – Statistics on <abbr title=\"New Enterprise Allowance\">NEA</abbr> including number of starts with a business mentor and the number of business starts. This statistical series has ended.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/provider-led-pathways-to-work-number-of-starts\">Provider-Led Pathways to Work</a> – Numbers of starts to the programme (now closed) and resulting job starts. This series ended in October 2011. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:hatti.archer@dwp.gov.uk\">hatti.archer@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pre-work-programme-and-get-britain-working\">Pre-Work Programme, New Enterprise Allowance, Youth Offer and Youth Contract</a> –  Statistics on pre-Work Programme mandatory programmes and work experience, sector-based work academies and Youth Contract Wage Incentives. This statistical series has ended.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/restart-scheme-statistics\">Restart Scheme</a> – Experimental statistics on people referred to and starting on the Restart Scheme.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cep.statistics@dwp.gov.uk\">cep.statistics@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/specialist-employability-support-statistics\">Specialist Employability Support</a> – the number of referrals to the programme and the corresponding numbers of starts and participants who find a job.\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:archer.halsejobshare@dwp.gov.uk\">archer.halsejobshare@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/troubled-families-statistics\">Troubled Families programme</a> – Statistics on benefits and employment for individuals and households on the programme. This statistical series has ended.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-choice-statistics-number-of-starts-and-referrals--2\">Work Choice: number of starts and referrals</a> – Numbers of referrals to the Work Choice programme, starts and participants who find a job.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:archer.halsejobshare@dwp.gov.uk\">archer.halsejobshare@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-programme-statistics--2\">Work Programme</a> – Statistics on people joining the Work Programme, participants achieving defined periods in work and participants completing the programme. This statistical series has ended.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-and-health-programme-statistics\">Work and Health Programme</a> – Statistics on people referred to and starting on the Work and Health Programme.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:epass.team@dwp.gov.uk\">epass.team@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/youth-unemployment-innovation-fund-pilot-statistics-and-evaluation\">Youth Unemployment Innovation Fund pilot</a> – Statistics on the pilot including number of participant starts, positive outcomes and evaluation findings. This statistical series has ended.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"equality-information\">Equality information</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/equality-and-diversity#equality-information\">Equality information</a> – Equality statistics on <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> employees and claimants  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:health.wellbeingandinclusion@dwp.gov.uk\">health.wellbeingandinclusion@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"health-disability-and-care\">Health, disability and care</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Attendance Allowance</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Carer’s Allowance</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/diffuse-mesothelioma-payment-scheme-statistics\">Diffuse Mesothelioma Payment Scheme</a> – Includes statistics on applications received, success rates and payment. This series ended in August 2019.  The information will continue to be published in the DMPS annual review.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:caxtonhouse.dmps@dwp.gov.uk\">caxtonhouse.dmps@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Disability Living Allowance</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Employment and Support Allowance (<abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>) summary</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-incapacity-benefits-reassessment\"><abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>: incapacity benefits reassessment (ceased)</a> – Statistics on the reassessment of incapacity benefits claimants for <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>. This series ended in November 2012.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-outcomes-of-work-capability-assessment\"><abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>: outcomes of Work Capability Assessment</a> – Work Capability Assessment outcomes for new <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> claims and incapacity benefits claims converted to <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions\"><abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> sanctions</a> – Number of sanctions imposed on people who receive <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:epass.team@dwp.gov.uk\">epass.team@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Incapacity Benefit</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/industrial-injuries-disablement-benefit-quarterly-statistics\">Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/life-opportunities-survey\">Life Opportunities Survey</a> – Data on how disabled and non-disabled people participate in society. This series ended in September 2015.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/opinions-and-lifestyle-survey-fulfilling-potential-outcomes-and-indicators\">Opinions and Lifestyle survey: ‘Fulfilling Potential’ outcomes and indicators</a>  <br>\nData measuring indicators in the Fulfilling Potential disability strategy outcomes and indicators framework. This series was last published in August 2015.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics\">Personal Independence Payment</a> – Includes numbers of claims in payment, new claim registrations, decisions and awards made.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:jess.arrowsmith@dwp.gov.uk\">jess.arrowsmith@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Severe Disablement Allowance</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/the-employment-of-disabled-people\">The employment of disabled people</a> – Detailed analysis and break downs of the number of disabled people in employment.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:mark.burley1@dwp.gov.uk\">mark.burley1@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-work-capability-assessment-statistics\">Universal Credit Work Capability Assessments</a> – Number of people on Universal Credit with a health condition or disability restricting their ability to work and the number (and outcomes) of Work Capability Assessment decisions made for Universal Credit.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:stats.consultation-2018@dwp.gov.uk\">stats.consultation-2018@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"housing-and-heating\">Housing and heating</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/social-fund-cold-weather-payments\">Cold Weather Payments</a> – Estimated number of Cold Weather Payments and total amounts paid.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:socialfundstrategy.singlepointofcontact@dwp.gov.uk\">socialfundstrategy.singlepointofcontact@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/discretionary-housing-payments-statistics\">Discretionary Housing Payments</a> – Statistics on local authorities’ use of Discretionary Housing Payment funds.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:keir.thomson@dwp.gov.uk\">keir.thomson@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/housing-benefit-and-council-tax-benefit-caseload-statistics--2\">Housing Benefit (<abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr>) and Council Tax Benefit</a> – Includes numbers receiving <abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> and the amount received. Council Tax Benefit data was provided to 2013. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/housing-benefit-caseload-statistics\"><abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> caseload</a> – Numbers of <abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> claimants.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/housing-benefit-entitlement-reductions-statistics\"><abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> entitlement reductions</a> – Statistics on <abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> entitlement reductions identified by local authorities as a proportion of expected reductions. This statistical series has ended.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:hbfe.performance@dwp.gov.uk\">hbfe.performance@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/experimental-housing-benefit-and-council-tax-benefit-flows-data-november-2008-to-present\"><abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> flows data</a> – Numbers of <abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> claims beginning and ending.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/housing-benefit-recoveries-and-fraud-data\"><abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> debt recoveries</a> – Data on incorrectly overpaid Housing Benefit (formerly <abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> recoveries and fraud)  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cbm.stats@dwp.gov.uk\">cbm.stats@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/housing-benefit-and-council-tax-benefit-statistics-on-speed-of-processing--2\"><abbr title=\"Housing Benefit\">HB</abbr> speed of processing</a> – Measure of the average time it takes to process a new claim or a change in circumstance of an existing claimant.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cbm.stats@dwp.gov.uk\">cbm.stats@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/support-for-mortgage-interest-statistics\">Support for Mortgage Interest statistics</a> - The number of households who are currently in receipt of the support as well as the number who have received Support for Mortgage Interest (<abbr title=\"Support for Mortgage Interest\">SMI</abbr>) loans so far.   <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:katie.wilkinson1@dwp.gov.uk\">katie.wilkinson1@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/winter-fuel-payments-caseload-and-household-figures\">Winter Fuel Payment</a> – Includes recipient and household data, and payments in EEA countries and Switzerland.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:wfp.statistics@dwp.gov.uk\">wfp.statistics@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"income-and-living-standards\">Income and living standards</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/below-average-resources-developing-a-new-poverty-measure\">Below Average Resources</a> – Official Statistics in Development outlining a new additional measure of poverty based on the approach proposed by the Social Metrics Commission.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:team.povertystats@dwp.gov.uk\">team.povertystats@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/children-in-out-of-work-benefit-households--2\">Children in out-of-work benefit households</a> – Numbers of children living in households where a parent or guardian claimed out-of-work benefits. This series ended in 2018</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/children-in-low-income-families-local-area-statistics\">Children in low income families: local area statistics</a> – Number and percentage of children living in relative and absolute low income families.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:russ.bentley@dwp.gov.uk\">russ.bentley@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/combined-working-age-absolute-low-income-and-material-deprivation-estimates-fye-2011-to-fye-2021\">Combined working age absolute low income and material deprivation estimates</a> – Experimental statistics on working-age adults in combined absolute low income and material deprivation. This statistical series has ended as a separate release. The statistics are now included in the annual <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/households-below-average-income-hbai--2\">Households Below Average Income (HBAI) releases</a>.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/family-resources-survey--2\">Family Resources Survey</a> – Facts and figures about the incomes and living circumstances of households and families in the <abbr title=\"United Kingdom\">UK</abbr>.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:team.frs@dwp.gov.uk\">team.frs@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/households-below-average-income-hbai--2\">Households below average income (HBAI)</a> – Number and percentage of people living in low-income households in the <abbr title=\"United Kingdom\">UK</abbr>. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:team.hbai@dwp.gov.uk\">team.hbai@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/income-dynamics-statistics\">Income dynamics</a> – Data on changes in incomes in the <abbr title=\"United Kingdom\">UK</abbr> including a measure of the extent to which people experience persistently low income.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:teamincome.dynamics@dwp.gov.uk\">teamincome.dynamics@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up--2\">Income-related benefits: estimates of take-up</a> – Estimates of the take-up of the main income-related benefits in Great Britain. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:irb.takeup@dwp.gov.uk\">irb.takeup@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Income Support</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions\">Income Support sanctions</a> – Number of sanctions imposed on people who receive Income Support. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:epass.team@dwp.gov.uk\">epass.team@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Pension Credit</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pensioners-incomes-series-statistics--3\">Pensioners’ Incomes series</a> – Annual statistics on pensioners’ incomes.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:pensioners-incomes@dwp.gov.uk\">pensioners-incomes@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"pensions-and-older-people\">Pensions and older people</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Attendance Allowance</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/social-fund-cold-weather-payments\">Cold Weather Payments</a> – Estimated number of Cold Weather Payments and total amounts paid. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:socialfundstrategy.singlepointofcontact@dwp.gov.uk\">socialfundstrategy.singlepointofcontact@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/economic-labour-market-status-of-individuals-aged-50-and-over\">Economic labour market status of individuals aged 50 and over</a> – Trends over time in the economic labour market status of individuals aged 50 and over.   <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:50pluschoices.analysis@dwp.gov.uk\">50pluschoices.analysis@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/dwp-benefit-statistics-dissemination-tools\">Neighbourhood statistics data: ward and super output area/data zone</a> – Numbers of <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit claimants within small geographical areas.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:judith.correia@dwp.gov.uk\">judith.correia@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/older-workers-statistical-information-booklet\">Older workers statistical information booklet (ceased)</a> – Labour market position of people aged 50 and over up to June 2013. This series ended in July 2015</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Pension Credit</a>  – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pension-credit-applications-and-awards\">Pension Credit applications and awards</a> –Statistics on the number of weekly Pension Credit claims received, cleared and awarded.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/national-insurance-contributions-statistics\">Pension provision (ceased)</a> – Statistics on people who qualify for State Pension and people with some kind of second tier pension cover. This series ended in April 2013.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:judith.correia@dwp.gov.uk\">judith.correia@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pensioners-incomes-series-statistics--3\">Pensioners’ Incomes series</a> – Annual statistics on pensioners’ incomes.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:pensioners-incomes@dwp.gov.uk\">pensioners-incomes@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">State Pension</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/winter-fuel-payments-caseload-and-household-figures\">Winter Fuel Payment</a> – Includes recipient and household data, and payments in EEA countries and Switzerland.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:wfp.statistics@dwp.gov.uk\">wfp.statistics@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/workplace-pension-participation-and-savings-trends\">Workplace pension participation and savings trends</a> – Workplace pension participation and saving trends, and estimates of the future impacts of automatic enrolment in them.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:workplacepensions.reformsevaluation@dwp.gov.uk\">workplacepensions.reformsevaluation@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"spending-fraud-and-error\">Spending, fraud and error</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/abstract-of-statistics-for-benefits-national-insurance-contributions-and-indices-of-prices-and-earnings\">Abstract of statistics</a> – Statistics on benefits, National Insurance contributions and indices of prices and earnings in Great Britain.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/benefit-cap-statistics\">Benefit cap</a> – Statistics on households affected by the benefit cap.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cbm.stats@dwp.gov.uk\">cbm.stats@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fraud-and-error-in-the-benefit-system\">Fraud and error in the benefit system</a> – Estimates of fraud and error levels in the benefit system in Great Britain.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:enquiries.fema@dwp.gov.uk\">enquiries.fema@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/unfulfilled-eligibility-in-the-benefit-system\">Unfulfilled eligibility in the benefit system</a> – Estimates of unfulfilled eligibility levels in the benefit system in Great Britain.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:enquiries.fema@dwp.gov.uk\">enquiries.fema@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"work-and-unemployment\">Work and unemployment</h3>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/get-britain-working-labour-market-insights\">Get Britain Working: Labour Market Insights</a> – These official statistics in development cover labour market insights.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/alternative-claimant-count-statistics\">Alternative Claimant Count statistics</a> – Number of people claiming unemployment related benefits. This series ended in October 2022.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/census-output-area-data-on-workless-benefit-claimants-2015\">Census output area data on workless benefit claimants</a> – Numbers of people by area claiming <abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>, Income Support and other income-related benefits. This series has been suspended and the latest data is for August 2015. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:judith.correia@dwp.gov.uk\">judith.correia@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/duration-on-working-age-benefits-statistics\">Duration on working-age benefits</a> – The length of time that claimants receive working-age benefits. This series ended in April 2016.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/economic-labour-market-status-of-individuals-aged-50-and-over\">Economic labour market status of individuals aged 50 and over, trends over time</a> – statistics on the economic labour market status of individuals aged 50 and over. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:50pluschoices.analysis@dwp.gov.uk\">50pluschoices.analysis@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Employment and Support Allowance (<abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>) summary</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-incapacity-benefits-reassessment\"><abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>: incapacity benefits reassessment (ceased)</a> – Statistics on the reassessment of incapacity benefits claimants for <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>. This series ended in November 2012.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-outcomes-of-work-capability-assessment\"><abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>: outcomes of Work Capability Assessment</a> – Work Capability Assessment outcomes for new <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> claims and incapacity benefits claims converted to <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr>. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions\"><abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> sanctions</a> – Number of sanctions imposed on <abbr title=\"Employment and Support Allowance\">ESA</abbr> claimants. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:epass.team@dwp.gov.uk\">epass.team@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/in-work-credit-statistics-on-start-ups--3\">In Work Credit (ceased)</a> – Take-up of the In Work Credit, a financial incentive available to lone parents moving into work. This series ended in May 2014.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistical-summaries\">Jobseeker’s Allowance (<abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>)</a> – Part of our <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit statistics.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk\">tonia.hagan@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions\"><abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr> sanctions</a> – Number of sanctions imposed on people who receive <abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:epass.team@dwp.gov.uk\">epass.team@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-statistics-on-the-six-month-offer--2\"><abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>: Six Month Offer</a> – Quarterly statistics detailing take-up of the Six Month Offer, a recruitment subsidy for job seekers that ended in March 2011. This series ended in October 2011.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-statistics-on-the-young-persons-guarantee-ypg\"><abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>: Young Person’s Guarantee (<abbr title=\"Young Person's Guarantee\">YPG</abbr>)</a> – Quarterly statistics on <abbr title=\"Young Person's Guarantee\">YPG</abbr>, which offers up to 24 weeks full-time training for unemployed young people. This series ended in April 2011.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/lone-parents-receiving-jsa-monthly-claimant-count\">Lone parents receiving Jobseeker’s Allowance</a> – Number of lone parents receiving <abbr title=\"Jobseeker’s Allowance\">JSA</abbr>. This series ended in May 2018.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/labour-market-status-by-ethnic-group-statistics\">Labour market status by ethnic group</a> – Statistics on labour market status by ethnic group. This series ended in April 2016.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/move-to-universal-credit-statistics\">Move to Universal Credit</a> – number of people who have been sent managed migration notices inviting them to claim Universal Credit.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:ucad.briefinganalysis@dwp.gov.uk\">ucad.briefinganalysis@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/national-indicators-statistics\">National Indicators</a> – Employment rates and ‘out of work benefits’ claimed by area. This series ended in May 2013.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/national-insurance-number-allocations-to-adult-overseas-nationals-entering-the-uk\">National Insurance number allocations to adult overseas nationals</a> – National Insurance number allocations by nationality at point of NINo registration of <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit recipients.  <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:cbm.stats@dwp.gov.uk\">cbm.stats@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/dwp-benefit-statistics-dissemination-tools\">Neighbourhood statistics data: ward and super output area/data zone</a> – Data on <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit claimants within small geographical areas.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/the-employment-of-disabled-people\">The employment of disabled people</a> – Detailed analysis and break downs of the number of disabled people in employment.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:mark.burley1@dwp.gov.uk\">mark.burley1@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics\">Universal Credit</a> – Number of people and households on Universal Credit, starts and claims made.    <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:team.ucos@dwp.gov.uk\">team.ucos@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions\">Universal Credit sanctions</a> – Number of sanctions imposed on people who receive Universal Credit. <br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:epass.team@dwp.gov.uk\">epass.team@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-work-capability-assessment-statistics\">Universal Credit Work Capability Assessments</a> – Number of people on Universal Credit with a health condition or disability restricting their ability to work and the number (and outcomes) of Work Capability Assessment decisions made for Universal Credit.<br>\nContact: <a href=\"mailto:stats.consultation-2018@dwp.gov.uk\">stats.consultation-2018@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics#dwp-statistics-and-contacts-by-theme\">Back to themes list</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"dwp-research\">\n<abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> research</h3>\n\n<p>As well as statistics, we also publish <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/research\">research and analysis</a>.</p>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evidence-and-evaluation-strategy-2025\">Evidence and Evaluation Strategy</a> sets out the department’s strategy for evidence and evaluation from 2025. It summarises how we generate and use evidence, what evidence we have, and how our evidence will drive delivery of our departmental priorities.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"dwp-benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables\">\n<abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> benefit expenditure and caseload tables</h3>\n\n<p>Our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/benefit-expenditure-tables\">benefit expenditure and caseload tables</a> provide historic and forecast expenditure and caseload information.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"contacts-general-enquiries\">Contacts: general enquiries</h2>\n\n<p>Contacts for <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> specific statistics are listed above.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"col\">General enquiries</th>\n      <th scope=\"col\">Contact</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>General statistical enquiries</td>\n      <td><a href=\"mailto:igs.foi@dwp.gov.uk\">igs.foi@dwp.gov.uk</a></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Forecasting, trends and projections</td>\n      <td><a href=\"mailto:expenditure.tables@dwp.gov.uk\">expenditure.tables@dwp.gov.uk</a></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Analytical tools and model development</td>\n      <td><a href=\"mailto:tim.knight@dwp.gov.uk\">tim.knight@dwp.gov.uk</a></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2 id=\"policies-and-procedures-for-dwp-statistics\">Policies and procedures for <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> statistics</h2>\n<p>We’ve published our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistics-policies-and-procedures\">policies and procedures for <abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> statistics</a> in the interests of transparency and to comply with the <abbr title=\"United Kingdom\">UK</abbr> Statistics Authority code of practice.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"pre-release-access-to-statistics\">Pre-release access to statistics</h2>\n<p>We’ve published the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/pre-release-access-to-statistics-order-2008\"><abbr title=\"Department for Work and Pensions\">DWP</abbr> arrangements for pre-release access to statistics</a> in the interests of openness and transparency. This provides details of  the job titles of everyone who has pre-release access and the organisations to which they belong.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions/about/statistics\">Back to top</a></p>\n\n</div>" .
